    &lt;Title&gt;First class care&lt;/Title&gt;
    &lt;ScreenName&gt;Anne&lt;/ScreenName&gt;
    &lt;CommentText&gt;I had general surgery on my wrist.  The operation took place the day  after my consultation and everyone from the receptionist to the nurses to the surgical staff were extremely friendly and looked after me from start to finish.  Even the Sister who had arranged the appointment popped into the waiting area to check that I was ok. 
 Every stage of the operation process was clearly explained to me, especially the anaesthetic process.  Operations can be scary but I felt calm and reassured throughout.  When I came round after the operation it was late in the day but there was no rush to discharge me before I was ready to get out of bed.  Truly first class care.  Thank you.&lt;/CommentText&gt;
